statement:
Let $X_1, X_2, \ldots, X_n$ represent a random sample from the discrete distribution having the pmf
$$
f(x;\theta)=\begin{cases}
\theta^{x}(1-\theta)^{1-x}, & x=0,1,\ 0<\theta<1,\\
0, & \text{elsewhere.}
\end{cases}
$$
Show that $Y_1=\sum_{i=1}^n X_i$ is a complete sufficient statistic for $\theta$. Find the unique function of $Y_1$ that is the MVUE of $\theta$.
